# Understanding JavaScript Classes

## JavaScript Class Syntax

```javascript
class Animal {
    constructor(name, age) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }
    speak() {
        console.log(`${this.name} makes a sound.`);
    }
}

// Instantiating an object
const dog = new Animal('Dog', 5);
dog.speak(); // Output: Dog makes a sound.
```

