# Inheritance in JavaScript Classes

## Implementing Inheritance

```javascript
class Animal {
    constructor(name) {
        this.name = name;
    }
    move() {
        console.log(`The ${this.name} moves.`);
    }
}

class Bird extends Animal {
    fly() {
        console.log(`The ${this.name} flies.`);
    }
}

const parrot = new Bird('Parrot');
parrot.move(); // Output: The Parrot moves.
parrot.fly();  // Output: The Parrot flies.
```

### Inheritance Flow Diagram:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Animal]
    B[Bird]
    A --> B
    A -->|Properties & Methods| C[move()]
    B -->|Extends| D[fly()]
```
